@page "/playground"
@using Eliterate.WebAssembly.Components.Generic
<PageTitle>Playground</PageTitle>

<div class="split">
    <div>
        <RotatingDisplay Paused="true">
            <PolaroidCamera RotateX="60" RotateZ="135">
                <img src="images/photos/Cat_on_tower.jpg" />
            </PolaroidCamera>
        </RotatingDisplay>
    </div>
    <div style="background-color:var(--color-background);padding:1rem;overflow-y:scroll;">
        <p>Did I build an entire 3d polaroid camera "model" in pure HTML/CSS just so I could pretend to print QR codes in the QR code generator I'm working on? That would be deeply idiotic! So much work for such little pay off... </p>
        <p style="margin-top:1rem;">Yeah. That's exactly what I did.</p>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    private string _input = "";
}
